  "prompt": "What are some good songs to prank my friend?",
  "response": "Pranking your friend with music can be hilarious, especially if the songs are unexpected, catchy, or just downright silly! Here are some fun song suggestions to mess with your friend:\n\n1. **\"Never Gonna Give You Up\" by Rick Astley**  \n   The ultimate prank song! Rickrolling never gets old.\n\n2. **\"Baby Shark\" by Pinkfong**  \n   This earworm will stick in their head for days\u2014perfect for a harmless prank.\n\n3. **\"What Does the Fox Say?\" by Ylvis**  \n   The absurdity of this song will have them questioning everything.\n\n4. **\"Barbie Girl\" by Aqua**  \n   A playful and catchy tune that\u2019s impossible not to react to.\n\n5. **\"It\u2019s Raining Men\" by The Weather Girls**  \n   Blast this at full volume for a hilariously dramatic effect.\n\n6. **\"Cotton Eye Joe\" by Rednex**  \n   A high-energy, country-dance track that\u2019s both catchy and ridiculous.\n\n7. **\"Call Me Maybe\" by Carly Rae Jepsen**  \n   This super catchy pop song is perfect to annoy them in a fun way.\n\n8. **\"Troll Song\" (The Troll Song) by Ylvis**  \n   Another Ylvis gem that\u2019s just as bizarre as \"The Fox.\"\n\n9. **\"I\u2019m Gonna Be (500 Miles)\" by The Proclaimers**  \n   A repetitive but infectiously upbeat tune that\u2019ll make them laugh.\n\n10. **\"Shake It Off\" by Taylor Swift**  \n    Play this if you want to get them dancing against their will.\n\n11. **\"Macarena\" by Los Del Rio**  \n    A classic throwback that\u2019ll have them doing the dance in no time.\n\n12. **\"Dragostea Din Tei\" by O-Zone (aka the \"Numa Numa\" song)**  \n    A viral hit that\u2019s fun and quirky.\n\n13. **\"All About That Bass\" by Meghan Trainor**  \n    A bouncy, feel-good song that\u2019s hard not to sing along to.\n\n14. **\"The Ketchup Song (Aserej\u00e9)\" by Las Ketchup**  \n    A quirky, nonsensical tune that\u2019s perfect for pranking.\n\n15. **\"What\u2019s New Pussycat?\" by Tom Jones**  \n    Trick them by playing this song on repeat\u2014bonus points if they don\u2019t expect it!\n\nFor an extra twist, you could curate a playlist of these songs and sneak it into their Spotify or play it on a shared device. Just make sure they have a good sense of humor and enjoy a laugh!",
